         <abstract id="aspace_b6f36eda7aafe0d6c0eee4abd371e3bd">The materials consist of photographs of Paul Wilkinson documenting the Yale campus during World War II. Included are photographs of facilities used by the armed services billeted on campus.</abstract>
         <origination label="creator">
            <persname identifier="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n2016010679"
                      source="naf">
               <part>Wilkinson, Paul</part>
            </persname>
         </origination>
    
      </did>
      <odd id="aspace_72d835b36b9e389a87914c995d369681">
         <head>General note</head>
         <p>Forms part of Yale Record Group 48-A (YRG 48-A), Yale pictorial records and collections.</p>  
      </odd>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_d362b4db26901740e9cf0c9120f7d119">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>The materials were a gift of Paul Wilkinson, 1989.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_ffc2d249cdf1a914fb92f171ef4e4892">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_27d41221c50cdd95c23fcd6c59c9b5e1">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Paul Wilkinson Photograph Collection Documenting Yale During World War II (RU 704). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <arrangement id="aspace_dfb39a1b82fd79bf67224633b794bc4b">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The photographs are arranged by building (region:chronology) number.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_5332ee91cb504243b09526139eb22fc6">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The materials consist of photographs of Paul Wilkinson documenting the Yale campus during World War II. Included are photographs of facilities used by the armed services billeted on campus.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
